The paper focuses on deep reinforcement learning for multiple agents in complex environments, with a particular emphasis on learning communication protocols. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The environments studied in the paper are inspired by communication riddles and computer vision problems, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
